name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: We are shattered. But we are grateful to the @MercerCoPros Homicide Task Force and Trenton PD for working around the clock to secure justice for Sequoya. We hold her loved ones and all those affected in our hearts, and vow to continue leading the fight to end gun violence in NJ.

name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: If this isn't a wake-up call, I don't know what is. It pained us to gather against the backdrop of another senseless act of gun violence - one that shouldn't have happened. Every child deserves to play outside safely, and no family should ever have to endure this type of tragedy.  https://t.co/KJJ5a2YCwD

name: Acting AG Matthew J. Platkin
tweet: @LimeyRat NJ Move Over applies to emergency vehicles displaying flashing lights and includes tow trucks, highway maintenance vehicles, and emergency service vehicles. Please protect all our highway workers. Slow down, move over, and stay safe!
